CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "An Array Of Stars - Pittsburgh's famous sons and daughters, who came home Thursday night to do a show for the Frogs at Syria Mosque, talk about old times in Smoky City. Mary Lou Williams is surrounded by (right to left) Maxine Sullivan, Billy Eckstine, Errol Garner, and Earl Hines. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Earl "Fatha" Hines, Erroll Garner, Billy Eckstine, Maxine Sullivan, and Mary Lou Williams at piano in Syria Mosque for Night of Stars
